From thread:
http://www.codeplex.com/PHPExcel/Thread/View.aspx?ThreadId=47951
 
After using insertColumn() method, you may find that the worksheet contains a spurious rowDimension with row index 0 (non-existing row).
 
This leads to Excel files generated by Excel5 writer having scroll bar that can be moved down to row ~ 65,636
 
Test:
----
$excel = new PHPExcel();
$sheet = $excel->getActiveSheet();
$sheet->setCellValue('A1', 'hello');
 
var_dump($sheet->getRowDimensions());
 
$sheet->insertNewColumnBefore('A', 1);
 
var_dump($sheet->getRowDimensions());
 
Expected result:
----
array(0) { }
array(0) { }
 
Actual result:
----
array(0) { }
array(1) { [0]=>  object(PHPExcel_Worksheet_RowDimension)#21 (5) { ["_rowIndex:private"]=>  int(0) ["_rowHeight:private"]=>  int(-1) ["_visible:private"]=>  bool(true) ["_outlineLevel:private"]=>  int(0) ["_collapsed:private"]=>  bool(false) } } 
 
Environment:
----
PHPExcel 1.6.5 (and latest source code)
